-- Egypt's SODIC posts jump in Q1 net profit 
-- By Asma Alsharif
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 03:53AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, June 5 (Reuters) - Egyptian property developer SODIC <OCDI.CA> posted a jump in first-quarter net profit, it said on Thursday.

The firm made 40.33 million Egyptian pounds ($5.64 million)in the three months ended March 31 compared with a net profit of 6.07 million pounds in the same period a year earlier, it said in a statement.